{"id": 23, "ts": 1778761255.5161974, "event": "public_discussion_message", "round": 1, "agent": "agent_3", "message": "Having gathered all the explicit facts that are available for each candidate, I can now weigh them against the selection criteria.\n**Candidate\u202fA**\n- **Strengths:** Anticipates dangerous situations, sees complex connections, excellent spatial vision, very good leadership qualities.\n- **Weaknesses:** Regarded as a show\u2011off, not open to new ideas, sometimes not good at taking criticism, can be unorganized. No explicit evidence of calmness under pressure or decision\u2011making speed, and the attitude issues suggest potential crew\u2011interaction problems.\n**Candidate\u202fB**\n- **Strengths:** Very conscientious, handles stress well, good at assessing weather conditions, excellent computer skills.\n- **Weaknesses:** Weak memory for numbers, makes nasty remarks about colleagues, can be grumpy and uncooperative. No data on decision\u2011making speed or calmness beyond stress handling; the interpersonal negatives are serious for teamwork.\n**Candidate\u202fC**\n- **Strengths:** Makes correct decisions quickly, stays calm in a crisis, understands complicated technology, 100\u202f% reliable, creates a positive atmosphere with his crew.\n- **Weaknesses:** Difficulty communicating ideas, regarded as egocentric, not very willing to further his education. Leadership ability is not directly described, but the positive crew atmosphere indicates at least functional teamwork.\n**Candidate\u202fD**\n- **Strengths:** Responds adequately to unexpected events, can concentrate very well, solves problems extremely well, takes responsibility seriously.\n- **Weaknesses:** Regarded as a know\u2011it\u2011all/arrogant, has a hot temper, relatively weak leadership skills. No explicit evidence of calmness under pressure; the temperament issues raise concerns for crew cohesion.\n**Evaluation against the criteria**\n| Criterion | A | B | C | D |\n|-----------|---|