ication and development concerns.\n**My vote:** Candidate C\nMETADATA_JSON:\n{\"agent\": \"agent_3\", \"vote\": \"Candidate C\"}", "thoughts": "We have gathered from both agents that there is no additional info beyond what we already have. So the shared mental model is complete.\n\nNow we need to produce our public contribution: we should evaluate candidates holistically, perhaps ask clarifying questions? But we have no more info. We can present our assessment and vote. We need to consider all candidates and weigh strengths/weaknesses.\n\nWe have the same info as other agents. Agent 1 voted Candidate C, Agent 2 voted Candidate A. We need to decide our own vote.\n\nWe should consider the criteria: reliability, technical competence, calmness, decision-making, teamwork, professional development.\n\nLet's weigh each:\n\nCandidate A: strong technical anticipation, spatial vision, leadership. Negatives: show-off, not open to new ideas, not good at taking criticism, unorganized. No data on calmness or decision speed. Teamwork concerns due to attitude. Professional development: resistance to new ideas.\n\nCandidate B: conscientious, handles stress, good weather assessment, computer skills. Negatives: weak memory for numbers (technical), nasty remarks, grumpy, uncooperative. No data on decision speed. Teamwork issues severe.\n\nCandidate C: quick correct decisions, calm in crisis, understands tech, 100% reliable, creates positive atmosphere. Negatives: difficulty communicating, egocentric, not willing to further education. Leadership unknown. Teamwork issues but positive atmosphere suggests some crew rapport. Professional development lacking.\n\nCandidate D: problem solving, concentration, responsibility, responds adequately to unexpected. Negatives: hot temper, know-it-all, weak leadership, arrogant. No calmness data. Teamwork issues likely.\n\nThus the best overall seems C: calm, reliable, quick decisions, technical, positive crew atmosphere. The communication difficulty and egocentric could be mitigated, but they are significant. However B's hostility is more severe. A's lack of calmness unknown, but attitude issues. D's hot temper is severe.\n\nThus I will vote Candidate C.\n\nNow produce public message summarizing reasoning, referencing known facts, and note that we have no additional info beyond shared mental model.\n\nProceed."}
